module.name: sap/ui/support/supportRules/ExecutionScope.js
module.description:
@class Allows to select the scope of analysis on an application.

Overview

ExecutionScope is the third parameter of a rule check function. It provides access to internal UI5 objects available for inspection. The getElements API method allows the user to select a specific subset of elements valid for their case. It accepts one query object argument.

Usage

When a rule is executed, three parameters are passed: oIssueManager, oCoreFacade and oScope. An ExecutionScope instance is passed to every call of a rule check function. When you analyze your application, available objects are collected depending on the settings passed to the Support Assistant at the moment when you start it. @public @since 1.48 @class sap.ui.support.ExecutionScope
